MOVEMENTS. MANAGEMENT DOES NOT BELIEVE ANY UNREALIZED LOSSES REPRESENT AN OTHER-THAN-TEMPORARY IMPAIRMENT BASED ON OUR EVALUATION OF AVAILABLE EVIDENCE AS OF JUNE 30, 2007.

COMMON AND PREFERRED STOCK AND OTHER INVESTMENTS THAT ARE RESTRICTED FOR MORE THAN ONE YEAR OR ARE NOT PUBLICLY TRADED ARE RECORDED AT COST. AT JUNE 30, 2007,

THE RECORDED BASIS AND ESTIMATED FAIR VALUE OF THESE INVESTMENTS WAS $38 MILLION. AT JUNE 30, 2006, THE RECORDED BASIS AND ESTIMATED FAIR VALUE OF THESE INVESTMENTS WAS $41 MILLION. THE ESTIMATE OF FAIR VALUE IS BASED ON PUBLICLY AVAILABLE

MARKET INFORMATION OR OTHER ESTIMATES DETERMINED BY MANAGEMENT.

