NOTE 14    EMPLOYEE STOCK AND SAVINGS PLANS

EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2005, WE ADOPTED SFAS NO. 123(R),

SHARE-BASED PAYMENT,

USING THE MODIFIED PROSPECTIVE APPLICATION TRANSITION METHOD. BECAUSE THE FAIR VALUE

RECOGNITION PROVISIONS OF SFAS NO. 123,

STOCK-BASED COMPENSATION,

AND SFAS NO. 123(R) WERE MATERIALLY CONSISTENT UNDER OUR EQUITY PLANS, THE ADOPTION OF SFAS NO. 123(R) DID NOT HAVE A SIGNIFICANT IMPACT ON OUR FINANCIAL

POSITION OR OUR RESULTS OF OPERATIONS. PRIOR TO OUR ADOPTION OF SFAS NO. 123(R), BENEFITS OF TAX DEDUCTIONS IN EXCESS OF RECOGNIZED COMPENSATION COSTS WERE REPORTED AS OPERATING CASH FLOWS. SFAS NO. 123(R) REQUIRES EXCESS TAX BENEFITS BE

REPORTED AS A FINANCING CASH INFLOW RATHER THAN AS A REDUCTION OF TAXES PAID.

THE STOCK-BASED COMPENSATION AND RELATED INCOME TAX BENEFITS WERE AS FOLLOWS.

